Due to this new accounting rule, the Net Loss for the bank was increased by $1,100 and Total Assets and Quarterly Average Assets were increased by $20,634. Tier 1 leverage ratio on 3-31-10 was 4.12% and Total Risk-Based Capital ratio was 10.85%. Excluding the effect of the FAS 166 items Tier 1 ratio would have been 4.96% and Total Risk-Based Capital ratio 14.24%. The participation structure on this credit was changed in the 2nd quarter, which will result in the additional Provision being reversed , and the asset and corresponding liability removed from the Balance Sheet.

In March 2007, the Bank received a one time allocation of $8.6 million in overhead. Effective 4/1/07, the Bank has entered into an agreement with its parent which states that the parent agrees not to allocate any overhead to the Bank until its net income, after allocation exceeds $2 million for a period of three years. Legg Mason Investment Council and Trust Company, NA ("Bank") now assesses and monitors its capital, capital needs and liquidity on a quarterly basis through its Investment Policy Committee. The Income and Expense sheet, Balance Sheet and Tier 1 Capital is reviewed monthly. As part of the quarterly financial review, the Bank's capital and liquidity is reviewed by the Board. In April 2010, the Bank increased its liquidity by $5 million.

Push-down purchase accounting created a Core Deposit Intangible asset in the amount of $1,120,000.  This intangible asset is amortized in accordance with GAAP and expensed resulting in a significant reduction in the reported earnings of the bank.  The earnings impact for the first 12-month period beginning 9/1/08 was $367,000.  The earnings impact for the second 12-month period beginning 9/1/09 is estimated to be $249,000. Accordingly in order to determine the tangible earnings of the bank, line 7.c.2. of schedule RI should be added back to the reported net income on line 14 of the same schedule.
